15/10/2010
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- EU foreign policy chief Catherine Ashton and US Secretary of State Hillary Clinton agreed on Thursday (October 14th) that the Balkan region has made progress in terms of reforms and Euro-Atlantic integration, but noted more needs to be done. They supported upcoming dialogue between Belgrade and Pristina, and voiced EU and US determination to help Bosnia and Herzegovina advance in its integration efforts. Clinton visited Brussels after wrapping up her tour of the Balkans. (Beta, B92, Tanjug - 14/10/10)
